BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:iM4gIg3P2HhHqHbHdY51N
SUMMARY:Veteran Service Provider Networking Hour
DTSTAMP:20260214T003622Z
DTSTART:20260224T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description Hello Fellow Providers\, Thank you to those who att
	ended last month&'s networking coffee hour event at MVCC. I love seeing th
	e depth of conversation and community we get in an in person setting. I've
	 been playing around with the name and date of this event\, but we decided
	 it might be more beneficial to plan these networking events around our Mi
	nority Veterans Training Program. So please feel free to come for the coff
	ee and networking and stay for a training on "Understanding and Honoring t
	he Black Military Experience. Which will begin at 1130. Coffee\, soft drin
	ks\, and snacks will be provided. What to expect: - Informal\, come-as-you
	-are networking - Connection with fellow Veteran service providers If you'
	re interested in attending\, hosting in the future\, or learning more\, I'
	d love to connect. Please feel free to share this invitation with colleagu
	es who may also benefit. Parking can be a little tight at the community ce
	nter at times. If the lot directly in front of the building is full\, ther
	e is an overflow lot just behind it. When you enter the building\, we are 
	located on the second floor all the way down past the elevators. The build
	ing is ADA accessible through the side entrance. I hope to see you there. 
	Please invite your colleagues.\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/veteran-service-provider-
	networking-hour/18089666/2026-02-24T00
LOCATION:Minority Vets Community Center\, 16040 Christensen Road\, Suite 21
	2\, Tukwila\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
